M
\mathbb{R}^{p,q}
n=p+q>2
b,c \in \mathbb{R}^{n}
\lambda \in \mathbb{R}
\omega \in \mathfrak{o}(p,q)
\lambda = c = \omega = 0
\tilde{b} \in \mathbb{R}^n
x
X^{\mu}(x) = 2 \langle x, b \rangle x^{\mu} - \langle x, x \rangle b^{\mu} + \lambda x^{\mu} + c + (\omega x)^{\mu}
Y^{\mu}(x) = 2 \langle x, \tilde{b} \rangle x^{\mu} - \langle x, x \rangle \tilde{b}^{\mu}
\mathfrak{o}(p+1,q+1)
